      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic continuum FEA with frictional contact is appropriate for ASTM F1717 compression-bending below yield; justification documented.",
      "rationale": "The model employs linear elastic material models for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) components and frictional contact at screw-rod and rod-connector interfaces. For the sub-yield loading regime of ASTM F1717 compression-bending, linear elasticity is well-established as appropriate. Geometric nonlinearity is included to capture large-displacement effects at 40 mm. Model form adequacy is supported by the validation comparisons."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test articles; uncertainty quantified.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and Poisson ratio for Ti-6Al-4V were taken from certified material test reports for the production lot used in bench testing. Screw and rod geometry were measured by coordinate measuring machine (CMM) with traceable calibration. Input uncertainty was propagated through Latin hypercube sampling (n=200) and found to contribute less than 2% to QoI variability."
    },
